Biography

2021 (Sophomore)

Played in eight games as a reserve defensive back and special teams contributor … Made five tackles, three of them at Toledo (career high) … Named to the NSU Athletics Director’s Honor Roll for the fall semester.

2020 (COVID)

NSU did not play due to COVID-19.

2019 (Freshman)

Played in 11 of the team’s 12 games as a true freshman … Made his mark on special teams and as a backup defensive back … Logged five tackles on the year, including two each against Virginia State and Coastal Carolina … NSU AD Honor Roll member for the spring semester.

High School/Prep

Spent one season playing for the prep team at Fork Union Military Academy … Was a four-year letterwinner in track and also played three years of varsity football at Atlee … Was a two-way starter at receiver and defensive back … Earned second-team all-region honors at receiver as a senior.

Personal

Cameron Joseph Foreman was born on July 11, 2000 … Son of Michael and Michelle Foreman … Majoring in sociology … Mother is an NSU alumna, and both his father and uncle played football at Hampton University.

Career Highs

Tackles: 3 (at Toledo, 9-4-21)
